  "body": "### Description\n*Type*: Bug\n\n*Summary*:  when you are trying to copy part of the text of long message, which should be scrolled automatically, it is not scrolled so you cannot see part of the selected text (overlapped by input field)\n\n#### Expected behavior\nthe message is automatically scrolled, all selected rows are visible\n\n#### Actual behavior\n![copy](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/42455613-6c4b297a-839b-11e8-85ff-9c9fb5b25d1d.png)\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- Open Status\n- Sign Up\n- Join any public or 1-1 chat\n- Send long (10+ rows) message\n- Scroll to the middle of the last message \n- Select visible rows + pull to select several rows overlapped by input field\n\n\n### Additional Information\n* Status version: desktop build 09/07/18 (after merge https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/5032)\n* Operating System: Mac OsX High Sierra\n* Video: [video](http://take.ms/cuCVF)",
